The paper deals with the performance analysis of multihop-intervehicular communication systems, which involves the study of information theory, networking, and communication engineering. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which can be related to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
